hich gives more flexibility when doing additional analysis with ppanggolin)\r\n\r\n# Bugfixes\r\n- fix a bug preventing you from doing a new clustering if partitions were not computed\r\n- fix genome sizes drawn with `draw --spots`"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/54258316", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/54258316/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/54258316/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/tag/1.2.46", "id": 54258316, "author": {"login": "axbazin", "id": 30264003, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwMjY0MDAz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/30264003?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin", "html_url": "https://github.com/axbazin", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "RE_kwDOBmr-FM4DO-qM", "tag_name": "1.2.46", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "PPanGGOLiN 1.2.46", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2021-11-29T16:39:32Z", "published_at": "2021-11-30T10:11:02Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/tarball/1.2.46", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/zipball/1.2.46", "body": "# New commands\r\n- `module` to predict conserved modules in variable parts of a pangenome\r\n- `context` to find which gene families are conserved in the same genomic context than sequences of interest\r\n- `all` to run all possible analysis with PPanGGOLiN.\r\n- `panmodule` to run the panModule workflow\r\n\r\n# Bug fixes\r\n- improved pseudogene reading and gff/gbff parsing\r\n- fixed gff parser to cope with bakta gff files (reported in #66)\r\n- fixed gexf formatting in the rare case of having '&' in the 'product' field of gene annotations (reported in #61)\r\n- fixed rare crash happening when a partition has only 1 gene family ( see #64 )\r\n- fixed compilation issue with gcc 10.* and above (reported in #69 )\r\n\r\n# Other:\r\n- Allow to compute K=2 if forced by the user in `partition` or `rarefaction`(by default, K is still picked between 3 and 20). (see #65 )\r\n- removed R, rpy2 and genoPlot-R dependencies (#47 shall never be a problem anymore)\r\n- added a new bokeh dependency\r\n- remove `spot --draw_hotspots` and related options. To realize the same thing, use `draw --spots` once the spots have been computed.\r\n- added a `--spots` option to `draw` to have interactive figures for spots of interest, replacing the former figures drawn with R.\r\n- `align` can compare a set of sequences of interest to a pangenome, and draw related elements, but cannot compare a genome to a pangenome anymore\r\n"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/38636649", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/38636649/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/38636649/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/tag/1.1.136", "id": 38636649, "author": {"login": "axbazin", "id": 30264003, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwMjY0MDAz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/30264003?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin", "html_url": "https://github.com/axbazin", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTM4NjM2NjQ5", "tag_name": "1.1.136", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "PPanGGOLiN 1.1.136", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2021-02-23T12:25:31Z", "published_at": "2021-02-24T09:36:11Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/tarball/1.1.136", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/zipball/1.1.136", "body": "Bug fixes:\r\n- cope with gff3 files without '##sequence-region' (such as Anvi'o 's and JGI's) (reported both in #48 and #56)\r\n- Do not create a new organism when reading fasta files for sequences when the organism was not in the previsouly read annotations (reported in #48) \r\n- For the 'msa' command, have the --phylo option actually working"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/37799267", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/37799267/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/37799267/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/tag/1.1.131", "id": 37799267, "author": {"login": "axbazin", "id": 30264003, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwMjY0MDAz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/30264003?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin", "html_url": "https://github.com/axbazin", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTM3Nzk5MjY3", "tag_name": "1.1.131", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "PPanGGOLiN 1.1.131", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2021-02-09T13:53:17Z", "published_at": "2021-02-15T08:50:41Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/tarball/1.1.131", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/zipball/1.1.131", "body": "* New 'fasta' command to write more easily fasta files of parts (or all ) of the pangenome (making #38 , along with other demands, possible)\r\n* New 'msa' command to compute MSA from specific families ( such as the core genome for additional phylogenetic analysis) (firstly suggested by #28 ). Will do so using only genes that are present in only one copy in each organism for each family.\r\n* Switching from lz4 to zstd for better compression for .h5 files (about 30% less disk space used with equivalent i/o speed)\r\n* More unit tests (Thanks to @sletort )\r\n\r\nBug Fixes\r\n* Cope with RAST-style gene identifiers (RAST gene identifiers were not used previously) (noticed in #44 )\r\n* Compute spots properly when the contig is circular (spots were not computed in circular contigs previously)(maybe fixes #43 ?) \r\n* Proper 'softcore' filter behavior when writing the gexf files (filter was too restrictive and did not include all softcore families)\r\n"}
