stering strategy\r\n- improved option checking\r\n\r\nBug fixes:\r\n- cope with contigs having identical identifiers in different genomes ( see #34 )\r\n- can change the duplication margin in 'rgp' without crashing\r\n- other minor technical bugs in 'align'"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/26507999", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/26507999/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/26507999/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/tag/1.1.85", "id": 26507999, "author": {"login": "axbazin", "id": 30264003, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMwMjY0MDAz", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/30264003?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin", "html_url": "https://github.com/axbazin", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTI2NTA3OTk5", "tag_name": "1.1.85", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "PPanGGOLiN 1.1.85", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2020-04-09T08:23:04Z", "published_at": "2020-05-14T12:01:40Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/tarball/1.1.85", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/zipball/1.1.85", "body": "- allows the extraction of spot borders\r\n- The gene_families.tsv now includes a third column with an 'F' if the gene is considered being a fragment of the gene family (--families_tsv option in the 'write' module)\r\n\r\nBug fixes : \r\n- fragment information is actually saved in the HDF5 file now (when using --defrag option with 'cluster', 'workflow' or 'panrgp')\r\n- cope with features not following the 'tag=value' when reading a gff3 file. They will now just be ignored. An error will be raised if a gff3 object does not have the required attributes. (see #29)\r\n- In case of an error due to file formatting when reading a cluster file (--clusters with 'cluster', 'workflow' or 'panrgp'), the error will now include the line number that caused the error (see #30)\r\n\r\n"}
