axbazin", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/axbazin/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "content_type": "application/gzip", "state": "uploaded", "size": 3463604, "download_count": 10, "created_at": "2019-11-07T10:54:58Z", "updated_at": "2019-11-07T12:15:17Z", "browser_download_url": "https://github.com/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/download/1.0.0/ppanggolin-1.0.0.tar.gz"}], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/tarball/1.0.0", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/zipball/1.0.0", "body": "New features:\r\n- Can choose the number of partitions in the 'workflow' subcommand\r\n- Can customize identity and coverage thresholds in the 'cluster' subcommand\r\n- Added 4 new possible outputs : \r\n                  - proteic fasta for representative sequences of the gene families\r\n                  - nucleic fasta for representative sequences of the gene families\r\n                  - nucleic fasta of all the CDS\r\n                  - a list containing the gene family IDs and the gene IDs alike the .tsv file format of MMseqs2\r\n- Added unit tests for the different classes thank to @sletort \r\n\r\nbug fixes :\r\n- Do not take into account the Markov Random Field if its criteria reaches infinity (problem of large dimensionality in statistics, PPanGGOLiN should crash less on VERY fragmented datasets.)\r\n- now properly reading .gbff/.gbk files\r\n- Improved compatibility for the .gexf files"}
{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/20244107", "assets_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/20244107/assets", "upload_url": "https://uploads.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/20244107/assets{?name,label}", "html_url": "https://github.com/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/releases/tag/v0.3.88", "id": 20244107, "author": {"login": "ggautreau", "id": 17834092, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE3ODM0MDky", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17834092?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau", "html_url": "https://github.com/ggautreau", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ggautreau/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "node_id": "MDc6UmVsZWFzZTIwMjQ0MTA3", "tag_name": "v0.3.88", "target_commitish": "master", "name": "Pre release version", "draft": false, "prerelease": false, "created_at": "2019-09-25T15:06:33Z", "published_at": "2019-09-25T13:17:17Z", "assets": [], "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/tarball/v0.3.88", "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/labgem/PPanGGOLiN/zipball/v0.3.88", "body": "PPanGGOLiN can annotate and build gene families by itself for an easier use, or use annotated genomes and formerly built gene families directly.\r\nPPanGGOLiN can have more than 3 partition and can estimate the optimal number of partitions.\r\nPPanGGOLiN can run parts of its pipeline separatly for better parameter tuning.\r\nPPanGGOLiN can provide a number of output files that will illustrate or describe your pangenome.\r\nPPanGGOLiN uses a HDF5 file to store all the informations related to a pangenome, and reuse or re-generate any of those data for further analysis.\r\nPPanGGOLiN makes a better use of CPUs in a multithreaded run.\r\nPPanGGOLiN can project the pangenome's partitions on a given protein set.\r\n\r\nPPanGGOLiN is compatible with macOS\r\n\r\nand a lot of bugfixes. (and maybe some new)\r\n"}
